-- BP Plc, Telenet Group: European Equity Market Preview
-- B y   J o s e p h   C i o l l i
-- 2012-04-25T04:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-24/bp-plc-telenet-group-european-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx  Europe  600 Index rose 1 percent to 254.37. The
 Stoxx 50 Index (SX5P)  increased 0.8 percent to 2,396.85. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro, gained
1.8 percent to 2,284.08.  BP Plc (BP/)  : A former engineer at Europe’s second-
largest oil firm, Kurt Mix, was arrested on charges of
intentionally destroying evidence requested by the U.S. about
the size of the 2010 Gulf of Mexico oil spill, in the first
criminal case arising from the incident. The shares rose 1.6
percent to 436.60 pence.  Telenet Group Holding NV (TNET)  : The Belgian cable
operator controlled by  Liberty Global Inc. (LBTYA)  bought back 159,000
shares from April 16 through April 24, for between 30.50 and
32.08 euros. The shares gained 0.4 percent to 31.90 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
